  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery boys look for when I exchange my old washing machine for a new one?",
  "response": "When Flipkart's delivery personnel come to exchange your old washing machine for a new one, they typically look for the following to ensure the exchange is valid and meets the criteria:\n\n**1. Physical Condition & Completeness:**\n\n*   **Presence of the Washing Machine:** Obviously, they need to confirm you actually have the washing machine you claimed you were exchanging.\n*   **Physical Damage:** They will inspect for significant physical damage beyond normal wear and tear.  This includes:\n    *   **Dents and Scratches:** While minor wear is expected, excessive dents, large scratches, or signs of significant impact damage may be a problem.\n    *   **Broken Parts:**  Broken knobs, doors, lids, or other crucial components.\n    *   **Rust and Corrosion:**  Extensive rust, especially in critical areas, can be a cause for rejection.\n    *   **Water Damage:** Obvious signs of significant water damage or flooding could be an issue.\n*   **Completeness of Components:** While this might depend on Flipkart's specific policy, they might expect essential components to be present:\n    *   **Inlet and Outlet Hoses:**  The hoses necessary to connect the machine to water and drainage.\n    *   **Power Cord:**  The original power cord.\n    *   **Filter(s):**  Important filters that came with the machine.\n    *   **Detergent Dispenser:**  The drawer or compartment where you put detergent.\n    *   **Internal Components (for certain cases):** They won't disassemble the machine, but if it's clearly missing major internal parts (like a visible motor), it will likely be rejected.\n\n**2. Functionality (Limited Check):**\n\n*   **Power On:** They might briefly check if the machine powers on.  They won't typically run a full wash cycle.\n*   **Basic Functionality:** They might turn the drum by hand to see if it rotates, especially for top-loading machines.  For front-loaders, they might check if the door latch works.\n*   **Overall Working Condition:** They might ask you about the machine's working condition (if it washes clothes, spins, etc.) but can't verify themselves.\n\n**3. Brand and Model Verification:**\n\n*   **Matching Details:** They'll verify that the brand and model number of the washing machine you're returning match the information you provided when you initiated the exchange.  This is usually done by checking the sticker on the machine.\n\n**4. Exchange Policy Compliance:**\n\n*   **Age of the Machine:** Flipkart might have a restriction on the age of the machine they'll accept for exchange.\n*   **Adherence to Exchange Terms:**  They will be looking to see if your exchange adheres to all the terms and conditions of the exchange offer you agreed to.\n\n**Important Considerations & Tips for a Smooth Exchange:**\n\n*   **Review Flipkart's Exchange Policy:** Before the delivery, carefully read Flipkart's exchange policy related to washing machines. This will tell you exactly what to expect and what their requirements are.\n*   **Honest Description:** Be honest about the condition of your washing machine when you initiate the exchange online. Don't exaggerate its condition.\n*   **Clean the Machine:**  Wipe down the machine and remove any loose items inside the drum.  A clean machine gives a better impression.\n*   **Be Prepared to Answer Questions:**  The delivery person may ask you questions about the machine's history or any known problems it has.\n*   **Document Any Damage:**  Take photos and videos of any existing damage before the delivery person arrives. This can be helpful in case of any disputes.\n*   **If Rejected, Understand Why:** If the exchange is rejected, ask the delivery person to explain the reason clearly. If you disagree, contact Flipkart customer support immediately.\n*   **Original Purchase Documentation:** While not always required, having your original purchase receipt or invoice handy can sometimes be helpful.\n\nBy being prepared and understanding what the delivery personnel are looking for, you can ensure a smoother and more successful exchange experience. Remember to always refer to Flipkart's specific exchange policy for the most accurate information.\n",
